# panel_add_node

Add a node to the user's OPEN ComfyUI graph by class_type (e.g. 'KSampler', 'CheckpointLoaderSimple'). The user sees it appear live; Ctrl+Z undoes it. Returns the created node's id, slots, and default widget values.

Parameters (JSON Schema):
{
 "type": "object",
 "properties": {
  "class_type": {
   "type": "string",
   "description": "Exact ComfyUI node class_type to create."
  },
  "pos": {
   "description": "Canvas [x, y] (two numbers). Auto-placed beside existing nodes when omitted.",
   "minItems": 2,
   "maxItems": 2,
   "type": "array",
   "items": {
    "type": "number"
   }
  },
  "title": {
   "description": "Optional custom node title.",
   "type": "string"
  }
 },
 "required": [
  "class_type"
 ],
 "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#"
}

Run it with: panel_call_tool {"name": "panel_add_node", "args": {...}}

# panel_search_nodes

Search installable custom-node packs via the user's BUILT-IN ComfyUI Manager (the same source the Manager UI uses). Returns matching packs {id, title, description}. Use the `id` with panel_install_node. Prefer this over the headless search_custom_nodes tool — it works against the user's actual (Desktop) Manager.

Parameters (JSON Schema):
{
 "type": "object",
 "properties": {
  "query": {
   "type": "string",
   "description": "Search text, e.g. 'kjnodes', 'controlnet', 'ipadapter'."
  },
  "limit": {
   "type": "integer",
   "minimum": 1,
   "maximum": 40
  }
 },
 "required": [
  "query"
 ],
 "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#"
}

Run it with: panel_call_tool {"name": "panel_search_nodes", "args": {...}}

